{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/create-ntp-server-using-ubuntu-14-04","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Network Time Protocol (NTP) is a networking protocol for time and date synchronisation between computers. By default, Windows 7 provides five servers (default being time.windows.com) to synchronise with. Time varies based on network latency however with tens of milliseconds over the Internet and almost one millisecond on LAN. Having a NTP server also reduces the amount of calls to the Internet made by hosts and achieves a better system time for all computers that rely on performance, integration and timeliness. Luckily a NTP server is very easy to build on Linux.</p>\n<!-- more -->\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-label=\"prerequisites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Internet connection</li>\n<li>Ubuntu 14.04</li>\n<li>Networking</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"ntp-installation-guide\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ntp-installation-guide\" aria-label=\"ntp installation guide permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NTP Installation Guide</h2>\n<p><strong>1.</strong> Install Ubuntu 14.04 LTS with roughly:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 CPU</li>\n<li>256MB RAM</li>\n<li>5GB HDD</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This will be all you need.</p>\n<p><strong>2.</strong> Install the NTP daemon using the command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token output\">sudo apt-get install ntp</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p><strong>3.</strong> Let's configure the NTP servers we are going to retrieve from. Edit the ntp.conf using the command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token output\">sudo nano /etc/ntp.conf</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>Here are the current servers that the service is currently retrieving the time from:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">server 0.ubuntu.pool.ntp.org\nserver 1.ubuntu.pool.ntp.org\nserver 2.ubuntu.pool.ntp.org\nserver 3.ubuntu.pool.ntp.org</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>This is something you should change to a local/country instead of the Ubuntu pools. You can find this at the <a href=\"http://www.pool.ntp.org\">NTP Pool Project</a>. I will be using the Australian pools so change the lines as necessary:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 253px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/212a230d0029a409b86ebf0eb0053889/09511/24.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 27.699530516431924%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"updated servers\"\n        title=\"updated servers\"\n        src=\"/static/212a230d0029a409b86ebf0eb0053889/09511/24.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/212a230d0029a409b86ebf0eb0053889/53f68/24.png 213w,\n/static/212a230d0029a409b86ebf0eb0053889/09511/24.png 253w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 253px) 100vw, 253px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Place the word <em>iburst</em> onto one pool to indicate you want to retrieve from this as soon as possible. This causes the daemon to synchronise with this server after starting up, otherwise it will take somewhere up to 20 minutes before the first synchronisation.</p>\n<p><strong>4.</strong> Add a fallback server. Ubuntu already provides their own fallback but we will use the current server's time as the default. Otherwise you can specify any other server you know of:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">server 127.127.1.0\nfudge 127.127.1.0 stratum 10</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 330px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c46856acc479e6eb273b5bf95af172b7/748ba/35.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 19.71830985915493%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"fallback server\"\n        title=\"fallback server\"\n        src=\"/static/c46856acc479e6eb273b5bf95af172b7/748ba/35.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c46856acc479e6eb273b5bf95af172b7/53f68/35.png 213w,\n/static/c46856acc479e6eb273b5bf95af172b7/748ba/35.png 330w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 330px) 100vw, 330px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>5.</strong> Your file will look something like this now:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 606px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4ed98d54f8551406bb450cf5aeb9351f/cec09/43.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.92488262910798%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"config\"\n        title=\"config\"\n        src=\"/static/4ed98d54f8551406bb450cf5aeb9351f/cec09/43.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4ed98d54f8551406bb450cf5aeb9351f/53f68/43.png 213w,\n/static/4ed98d54f8551406bb450cf5aeb9351f/df70d/43.png 425w,\n/static/4ed98d54f8551406bb450cf5aeb9351f/cec09/43.png 606w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 606px) 100vw, 606px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Hit <em>CTRL+X</em>, enter <em>Y</em> to confirm and hit Enter.</p>\n<p><strong>6.</strong> Restart the daemon service using the command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token output\">sudo /etc/init.d/ntp restart</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p><strong>7.</strong> Monitor the log to see when it starts synchronising using the command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token output\">tail -f /var/log/syslog</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p>(Ctrl + C to exit)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7684b322ca8074041f66ce3b8cb29898/78d47/53.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"restart server\"\n        title=\"restart server\"\n        src=\"/static/7684b322ca8074041f66ce3b8cb29898/78d47/53.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7684b322ca8074041f66ce3b8cb29898/53f68/53.png 213w,\n/static/7684b322ca8074041f66ce3b8cb29898/df70d/53.png 425w,\n/static/7684b322ca8074041f66ce3b8cb29898/78d47/53.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>8.</strong> It nothing comes up (which usually happens to me), run the command '<em>ntpq -p</em>' and it should show you all the time servers you are currently connecting with. This is enough to know if it is synchronized for now.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell-session\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-shell-session line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-shell-session\"><span class=\"token output\">ntpq -p</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 634px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a14c23213240571fd0ea42468a11040d/54e75/63.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.535211267605636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"polling server\"\n        title=\"polling server\"\n        src=\"/static/a14c23213240571fd0ea42468a11040d/54e75/63.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a14c23213240571fd0ea42468a11040d/53f68/63.png 213w,\n/static/a14c23213240571fd0ea42468a11040d/df70d/63.png 425w,\n/static/a14c23213240571fd0ea42468a11040d/54e75/63.png 634w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 634px) 100vw, 634px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>9.</strong> Find the hostname of the server (<em>hostname -A</em>) or its IP address (<em>ifconfig</em>) and start synchronising everything!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 443px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/650ee2c74f47f93552bd3e8b465b3d16/4d697/71.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.154929577464785%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"sync with ntp server\"\n        title=\"sync with ntp server\"\n        src=\"/static/650ee2c74f47f93552bd3e8b465b3d16/4d697/71.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/650ee2c74f47f93552bd3e8b465b3d16/53f68/71.png 213w,\n/static/650ee2c74f47f93552bd3e8b465b3d16/df70d/71.png 425w,\n/static/650ee2c74f47f93552bd3e8b465b3d16/4d697/71.png 443w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 443px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6319a8b0a59a71015fedaea04e233cf9/4d697/91.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 59.154929577464785%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"sync using FQDN\"\n        title=\"sync using FQDN\"\n        src=\"/static/6319a8b0a59a71015fedaea04e233cf9/4d697/91.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6319a8b0a59a71015fedaea04e233cf9/53f68/91.png 213w,\n/static/6319a8b0a59a71015fedaea04e233cf9/df70d/91.png 425w,\n/static/6319a8b0a59a71015fedaea04e233cf9/4d697/91.png 443w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>If the hostname does not work, try the IP address. If that works then use '<em>ipconfig /flushdns</em>' to clear your cache and make Windows retrieve the hostname from the DNS instead of the cache.</p>","timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"Network Time Protocol (NTP) is a networking protocol for time and date synchronisation between computers. By default, Windows 7 provides…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/calvin.me/calvin.me/master/posts/2014-09-24-create-ntp-server-using-ubuntu-14-04/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Create an NTP Server using Ubuntu 14.04","categories":["Networking","Computers"],"tags":["linux","ntp","ubuntu"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fixed","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/17416f667d8d61d202cf8b2d50e3638a/ccc8a/thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/17416f667d8d61d202cf8b2d50e3638a/ccc8a/thumbnail.png 150w,\n/static/17416f667d8d61d202cf8b2d50e3638a/67d4a/thumbnail.png 300w","sizes":"150px"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/17416f667d8d61d202cf8b2d50e3638a/3554d/thumbnail.webp 150w,\n/static/17416f667d8d61d202cf8b2d50e3638a/c437f/thumbnail.webp 300w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"150px"}]},"width":150,"height":150}}}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-create-ntp-server-using-ubuntu-14-04\\/.*$/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}